p: Supplementary Figure S1 shows the effects of different lipid sources on growth of juvenile swimming crab. There were no statistical differences in survival of swimming crab juveniles among all diets ( P > 0.05). It was found that crabs fed KO diet had a significantly higher PWG (percent weight gain) and MR (molting ratio) than those fed other diets ( P < 0.05), followed by FO diet.
